President Biden has announced his intention to appoint a group of qualified and diverse leaders to the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs). This board will support the HBCU Initiative, which aims to enhance the capacity of HBCUs to provide high-quality education and opportunities for students. The Biden-Harris Administration has already committed over $5.8 billion in support to HBCUs through initiatives like the American Rescue Plan and debt forgiveness for capital improvement projects. The individuals being appointed to the board include Dr. Makola M. Abdullah, Javaune Adams-Gaston, Paige Blake, Thasunda Brown Duckett, Willie A. Deese, Patrick Cokley, Dr. Monica Goldson, Brett Hart, Taraji P. Henson, Beverly W. Hogan, Lisa P. Jackson, Florida State Senator Shevrin Jones, Dr. Walter M. Kimbrough, William F. L. Moses, NBA player Chris Paul, Dr. Quinton T. Ross Jr., Ruth J. Simmons, and Janeen Uzzell. Each of these individuals brings a unique set of qualifications and experiences to contribute to the advancement of HBCUs.